---
import desktopImage from "../assets/img/EosOS-plasma-descktop.png";
import desktopIcon from "../assets/img/pc.png";
import installIcon from "../assets/img/install.png";
---

<section id="home">
  <div class="container">
    <h1>Welcome to EosOS Linux KDE Lite</h1>
    <p>
      Independent distribution based on Arch Linux, easy to use and highly
      customizable.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<section id="requirements">
  <div
    class="card flex flex-row items-center bg-[rgba(31, 31, 48, 0.6)] backdrop-blur-md rounded-2xl gap-4 w-full max-w-7xl p-8"
  >
    <div class="flex flex-col justify-center align-middle w-[65%]">
      <h2 class="font-bold title">System Requirements</h2>
      <table class="text-left">
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Component</th>
            <th>Minimum</th>
            <th>Recommended</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td>Processor</td>
            <td>64-bit</td>
            <td>64-bit</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>RAM</td>
            <td>4 GB</td>
            <td>8 GB</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Disk Space</td>
            <td>80 GB</td>
            <td>120 GB</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Disk Type</td>
            <td>HDD</td>
            <td>SSD</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Graphics</td>
            <td>OpenGL 3.0 compatible</td>
            <td>OpenGL 4.5 compatible</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Network</td>
            <td>Internet connection</td>
            <td>Internet connection</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
    <div class="flex justify-center items-center mt-4">
      <img
        src={desktopIcon.src}
        alt="EosOS KDE Desktop"
        class="card-image w-full h-auto"
      />
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section id="dowonload" class="flex-col">
  <div
    class="card flex flex-row items-center bg-[rgba(31, 31, 48, 0.6)] backdrop-blur-md rounded-2xl gap-4 w-full max-w-7xl"
  >
    <div class="card-image-wrapper flex justify-center items-center">
      <img
        src={desktopImage.src}
        alt="EosOS KDE Desktop"
        class="card-image rounded-l-2xl w-full h-auto"
      />
    </div>

    <div class="card-text p-8 flex flex-col justify-center align-middle">
      <h2 class="text-center font-bold">EosOS Linux KDE Lite</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Independent distribution based on Arch Linux</li>
        <li>Easy to use</li>
        <li>Highly customizable for everyone</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="text-center">
        <a
          href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/1ReaIxGbM7bUcvPehicN_f72Ygekn0BOQ/view?usp=drive_link"
          class="card-button"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
        >
          Download
        </a>
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <p class="text-center text-gray-400 mt-4">
    sha256sum: b26bcb72eafd618f748fc49ca3c8b252a8c9a7e7f4538bd958d07ca5287827b6
  </p>
</section>

<section id="install">
  <div class="card flex flex-row items-center bg-[rgba(31, 31, 48, 0.6)] backdrop-blur-md rounded-2xl gap-4 w-full max-w-7xl">
    <div class="flex flex-col justify-center items-center content-center textt-center">
      <h2 class="title">Installation procedure</h2>
      <img
        src={installIcon.src}
        alt="Installation procedure"
        class="card-image rounded-l-2xl w-full h-auto"
      />
    </div>
    <div >
      <div>
        <div class="text-md mb-5 mt-10 sm:px-10 md:px-24 lg:px-36 flex">
          <div class="m-auto my-10 md:my-auto">
            </div>
            <div class="ml-20">
              <p>Boot the PC and press the manufacturer specific key to open your device's setup utility. Common keys used: Esc, Delete, F1, F2, F9, F10, F11, or F12.</p>
              <a href="https://searx.garudalinux.org/search?q=BIOS%20menu%20key%20brand&amp;categories=general" rel="noopener" target="_blank" class="text-justify text-primary">Find more common keys and buttons <i class="pi pi-external-link" style="font-size: 0.7rem;"></i></a>
              <hr class="my-4">
              <p>Disable fastboot and secure boot. It may not be possible to disable the latter explicitly - try clearing the secure boot keys instead. Check the manual of your device/motherboard for further info.</p>
              <hr class="my-4">
              <p>Make sure that your device's SATA controller is set to AHCI mode in your device's setup utility - otherwise, the Linux kernel may not be able to detect your drive.</p>
              <hr class="my-4">
              <p>If your firmware supports UEFI, then configure your device to use UEFI only in its setup utility. UEFI is much preferred over BIOS whenever possible.</p>
              <hr class="my-4">
              <p>Create a bootable USB using DD/Etcher/Ventoy/Rufus. Ventoy is the easiest method and allows multiple editions on the one USB, while DD/Etcher the most reliable.</p>
              <hr class="my-4">
              <p>Boot from the USB drive. When using Ventoy make sure to use the "GRUB2" option in the boot menu.</p>
              <hr class="my-4">
              <p>After booting the live media, start the installer and follow the guided installation procedure.</p>
              <hr class="my-4">
              <p>The login credentials are:</p>
              <ul class="text-center">
                <li>Username: <a class="font-mono">garuda</a></li>
                <li>Password: <a class="font-mono">garuda</a></li>
              </ul>
              <hr class="my-4">
              <p>While the installation is running, please consider reading the following recommendations.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  #home {
    padding-top: 80px; /* Altura navbar + margen */
    padding-bottom: 3rem;
    text-align: center;
  }

  #home h1 {
    font-size: 3rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    color: #e6b2bb;
  }

  #home p {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    max-width: 600px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    color: #ccc;
  }
</style>
